                                      Advantages

1.Based on Python, which is the extremely powerful given it’s library rich nature.
2.Write code once and use it across all devices.
3.Easy to use widgets built with multi-touch support.
4.Performs better than HTML5 cross-platform alternatives.










                                              Disadvantages

1.Non-native looking User Interface.

2.Bigger package size (because Python interpreter needs to be included).

3.Lack of community support (Kivy Community isn’t particularly large).

4.Lack of good examples and documentation.

5.Better and more community rich alternates available if only focusing on Mobile Cross-platform
  devices i.e React Native.